articles.author: Jonathan Landay, Phil Stewart, Anthony Deutsch
articles.description: Iran did not include mobile launchers with the close-range ballistic missiles that Washington last week accused Tehran of delivering to Russia for use against Ukraine, according to three sources with knowledge of the matter.
articles.title: Exclusive: Iran withheld launchers for missiles sent to Russia, sources say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: At least 31 people died in an Israeli airstrike on a Beirut suburb on Friday, the Lebanese health ministry said on Saturday, including three children and seven women, in the deadliest strike in a year of conflict between Hezbollah and Israel.
articles.title: Israeli strike on Beirut on Friday killed 31, Lebanese ministry says

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Palestinians said an Israeli strike killed at least 22 people in a school sheltering displaced people in southern Gaza City on Saturday, while the Israeli military said the attack targeted a Hamas command centre.
articles.title: Palestinians say Israeli strike killed 22 in shelter, army says it hit militants

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Iran's Supreme Leader, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, said on Saturday that Israel is committing "shameless crimes" against children, not combatants.
articles.title: Iran's Supreme Leader says Israel is committing 'shameless crimes' against children

articles.author: Trevor Hunnicutt, David Brunnstrom
articles.description: Leaders of Australia, India, Japan and the United States will announce plans for new security initiatives in the Indian Ocean on Saturday, when outgoing U.S. President Joe Biden hosts counterparts from the Quad grouping established due to shared concerns about China.
articles.title: Quad to expand maritime security cooperation at Biden's farewell summit

articles.author: Elias Biryabarema
articles.description: The son of Uganda's long-serving leader Yoweri Museveni said on Saturday he had abandoned plans to run for presidency at the next election in 2026, urging his supporters to endorse his father instead.
articles.title: Son of Uganda's president ends 2026 election bid

articles.author: Valerie Volcovici, Kate Abnett
articles.description: Countries could use next week's U.N. meetings in New York to resolve big differences over boosting the world's annual goal for climate finance, but uncertainty over the U.S. election could jeopardize progress ahead of the next U.N. climate summit in November.
articles.title: US election uncertainty clouds UN climate finance progress

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Hungarian intelligence services have conducted several interviews with the CEO of BAC Consulting, a Budapest-based company linked to deadly explosions of pagers used by Hezbollah members this week, the Hungarian government said on Saturday.
articles.title: Hungarian intelligence agency interviewed CEO linked to exploding Hezbollah pagers

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Cyprus's president called for restraint over escalating tensions in the Middle East in separate telephone conversations with the Lebanese and Israeli prime ministers on Saturday, his spokesperson said in a statement.
articles.title: EU member Cyprus calls on Lebanon, Israel to show restraint in Middle East

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: President Volodymyr Zelenskiy said he hoped to meet Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump next week when he travels to the United States to present Ukraine's "victory plan" in the war against Russia.
articles.title: Ukraine's Zelenskiy hopes to meet Donald Trump next week
